  "body": "## Description\r\nThere is a bug in the events API, specifically when subscribing to multiple events. The [Beacon-API spec](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/#/Events/eventstream) specifies that the URL for subscribing to multiple events should be in the form of `/eth/v1/events?topics=<topic1>&topics=<topic2>`. This is currently not the case.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n`Lighthouse/v2.0.1-fff01b2/x86_64-linux`\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\nIf we want to subsribe to both `block` and `finalized_checkpoint` subscriptions, the API only works with the following request: `/eth/v1/events?topics=block,finalized_checkpoint`. This does not conform to the spec.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\nAccording to the beacon spec, the URL should be the following: `/eth/v1/events?topics=block&topics=finalized_checkpoint`.",
